api_list.name: listCustomers
api_list.description: List all customers

optional_parameters.name: customer
optional_parameters.description: If true then the resulting people list will be filtered to only include those who have placed an order, if false then the resulting list will only include people who have not placed an order

optional_parameters.name: orderCountLess
optional_parameters.description: Filters the resulting list to only include customers who have ordered less than the specified number of times

optional_parameters.name: createdBefore
optional_parameters.description: Filters the resulting list to only include those people created before the specified date time

optional_parameters.name: pushTokenIsset
optional_parameters.description: If true filters the resulting list to only include people with push notification tokens, if false filters the resulting list to only include people without push notification tokens

optional_parameters.name: lastOrderedDateLess
optional_parameters.description: Filters the resulting person list to only include people that have ordered less recently that the value. Valid values include Ndays, Nweeks, Nmonths where N is a number. E.g. 1days / 7weeks.

optional_parameters.name: lastOrderedDateMore
optional_parameters.description: Filters the resulting person list to only include people that have ordered more recently that the value. Valid values include Ndays, Nweeks, Nmonths where N is a number. E.g. 1days / 7weeks.

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: By default, you get returned a paginated set of objects (20 per page is the default), by specifying the limit argument you can control the number of objects returned

optional_parameters.name: orderCountMore
optional_parameters.description: Filters the resulting list to only include customers who have ordered more than the specified number of times

optional_parameters.name: livePerson
optional_parameters.description: If true filters the resulting person list to only include people created in the live environment, if false filters the resulting person list to only include people created in the test environment

optional_parameters.name: offset
optional_parameters.description: The offset into the result set of objects returned

optional_parameters.name: country
optional_parameters.description: Array of 3 digit country codes i.e. GBR,USA that will filter the resulting person list to only include people coming from the specified countries

api_list.name: listOrders
api_list.description: List all orders

optional_parameters.name: timeSubmitted
optional_parameters.description: GTE datetime. Orders will be filtered to only include those that were placed after this date & time

optional_parameters.name: orderBy
optional_parameters.description: Controls the ordering of the returned orders, valid options are time_submitted & status. A - can be added to the front of any option i.e. -time_submitted to reverse the ordering.

optional_parameters.name: errorExclude
optional_parameters.description: If true then results will be filtered to only include successful orders, if false then only orders for which an error has occured will be returned

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: By default, you get returned a paginated set of objects (20 per page is the default), by specifying the limit argument you can control the number of objects returned

optional_parameters.name: offset
optional_parameters.description: The offset into the result set of objects returned

optional_parameters.name: refundRequested
optional_parameters.description: If true then results will be filtered to only include orders for which the customer has requested a refunded, if false then only orders for which there has been no refund request

optional_parameters.name: testOrder
optional_parameters.description: If true then the results will be be filtered to only include test orders, if false then only live orders will be returned

api_list.name: searchAddressByAddressId
api_list.description: You can perform a search on any part of the address not just the ZIP/Postal code and our smart sorting of results will order by nearest locations first. We also recognise common misspellings.

required_parameters.name: addressId
required_parameters.description: A parameter referencing a previously returned address search results list item that can be used to lookup a unique address.

required_parameters.name: countryCode
required_parameters.description: Three letter country code to which the address search will be restricted

api_list.name: searchAddressBySearchTerm
api_list.description: You can perform a search on any part of the address not just the ZIP/Postal code and our smart sorting of results will order by nearest locations first. We also recognise common misspellings.

required_parameters.name: countryCode
required_parameters.description: Three letter country code to which the address search will be restricted

required_parameters.name: searchTerm
required_parameters.description: A free text value, often encompassing the first line of address or ZIP/Postal code, on which the search is performed.
